Date: Sat 17 Jul 2004
From: Holly Tunning Canfield <hdt@runewolf.net>
Source: WDTV News, Fri 16 Jul 2004 [edited]

West Virginia: 2 Cases of Hantavirus Pulmonary Syndrome, One Fatal
---------------------------------------------------
I have no other information, but I saw in our local news WDTV last night
that West Virginia has a confirmed case of hantavirus pulmonary
syndrome. A male patient is being treated at Ruby Memorial Hospital or WVU
Hospital in Morgantown, WV. They also reported that a Virginia man died on
Fri 16 Jul 2004 [8 Jul 2004 according to the following report - Mod.CP]
from hantavirus pulmonary syndrome believed to have been contracted while
he was doing research in West Virginia.
According to the CDC website, hantavirus pulmonary syndrome was first found
in West Virginia in June of 1993, at the same time as it was found in the
Southwest, US. These 2 cases will be the 2nd and 3rd confirmed cases in
West Virginia.
--
Holly Tunning Canfield
Vet Tech Student
Fairmont State College
